ns on women\u2019s travel. National Network Group Against Trafficking is a 98-member NGO pressure group, formed to lobby against trafficking. Alliance Against Trafficking in Women and Children in Nepal de-links trafficking from sex work, migration, and HIV, and is beginning to develop a safe migration emphasis. 107 NEPAL The Global Fund to Fight AIDS, Tuberculosis and Malaria is an international financing institution whose primary objective is to halt three of the world\u2019s most devastating diseases. GFATM is supporting a large programme on HIV and migration in Nepal. 108 Recommendations The following recommendations are made within the context of the foregoing analysis of Nepal\u2019s migration patterns and policies and HIV situation.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "c9923581-e6fe-49ec-bb1c-6f28bf0363d8": {"__data__": {"id_": "c9923581-e6fe-49ec-bb1c-6f28bf0363d8", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/hiv-and-mobility-south-asia", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "HIV and Mobility in South Asia", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/hiv-and-mobility-south-asia", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "b409e05c673c1e5b97d08f3b8d02d936d1948091e593d75e39495131bb19781d"}, "2": {"node_id": "4c3f6877-0b16-4ea3-a80b-dc0fd3d25b7b", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/hiv-and-mobility-south-asia", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "c368b49bd57cee5a4f24fb29798943b33b78515dc302c9c92aa98e0c6fa1c0f1"}}, "hash": "d2e42707cdff5250ff07d0ddc2f1377b0e874bc088fc772b14933ab7fc047e6e", "text": "In order to reduce the HIV vulnerability of current and future migrant and mobile populations it will be necessary to take action in a range of key areas, as detailed below. 1. Ratify the 1990 UN International Convention on the Protection of the Rights of All Migrant Workers and Members of Their Families as well as the UN Protocol to Prevent, Suppress and Punish Traffi cking in Persons. Accordingly, add a provision for protection of", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "9de73ce4-4ef5-495e-bdd5-0dde3bdc1d5b": {"__data__": {"id_": "9de73ce4-4ef5-495e-bdd5-0dde3bdc1d5b", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/hiv-and-mobility-south-asia", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "HIV and Mobility in South Asia", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/hiv-and-mobility-south-asia", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "40d95854b6dc9317efde68d68457f96985203ec3990f8ab4657365797be9a0b1"}, "3": {"node_id": "0a77befb-5b0f-4dc4-bf9e-53453a06e8b5", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/hiv-and-mobility-south-asia", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "104044c1a449bfe7850859d4fcb03e71ad78b07279aa82ceafd5ebe02b4e