tlook. 17 Current exchange rate US$:LKR (Lanka Rupee) is 108.29. 18 Central Bank of Sri Lanka, Economic and Financial Statistics. ineligible to receive government welfare transfers once a member of the family migrates.19 Not all migrant remittances are processed through the banking system and official channels. Informal transfer mechanisms are discouraged by the government, and the extent of these money transfers is unknown. Earnings are also repatriated in the form of goods brought home by returning migrants. HIV/AIDS Situation The first case of HIV in Sri Lanka was detected in 1987. As of the end December 2009 the estimated number of people living with HIV was 3000, and a cumulative total of HIV cases, 1,196, had been reported to the National STD and AIDS Control Program (NSACP), the majority of which were in the 25-49 age group. Estimated HIV 19 UNDP, \u201cHIV Vulnerabilities of Women Migrants,\u201d 2009. SRI LANKA Table 3: Destination Countries for Sri Lankan Migrant Workers 2003 to 2008 Destination 2003 2004 2005 2006 2007 2008 Saudi Arabia 36.26% 33.21% 32.95% 30.42% 27.69% 26.90% Kuwait 18.41% 17.12% 15.63% 17.18% 18.78% 18.72% U.A.E. 15.40% 15.32% 15.72% 16.74% 17.86% 20.57% Qatar 11.34% 13.98% 15.54% 15.58% 17.83% 15.69% Source: SLBFE, Annual Statistical Report of Foreign Employment, 2008.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "a91a6642-c5c4-4a0e-8535-0509e18e3a4b": {"__data__": {"id_": "a91a6642-c5c4-4a0e-8535-0509e18e3a4b", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/hiv-and-mobility-south-asia", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "HIV and Mobility in South Asia", "node_type"