u2019 imprisonment. Philippines Legal Legal since 1823. Singapore Illegal Penal Code section 377A. Act of gross indecency by male with another male person. Thailand Legal Legal since 1956. Timor-Leste Legal Legal since 1975. Viet Nam Legal Penal Code, article 115. Age of consent to homosexual sex and heterosexual sex is 16 years. 30 HIV AND THE LAW IN SOUTH-EAST ASIA CHAPTEr 4: MSM AND TrANSgENDEr Law on Pornography 59 defines homosexuality as a deviant form of behaviour, and some subnational laws prohibit sex between men or conflate homosexual conduct with prostitution.60 Law enforcement practices A review conducted in 2010 found numerous examples of law enforcement abuses against MSM and transgender people in South-East Asian countries, such as extortion and police harassment and violence, including in Cambodia, Indonesia, Malaysia, and Myanmar.61 Such incidents can deter MSM and transgender people from attending HIV services or disclosing their sexuality or gender identity to health services due to fear of discrimination. Several initiatives have been taken to improve relations between police and MSM and transgender communities. In Cambodia, the Police Community Partnership Initiative is working to improve the relations between police and communities of MSM and transgender people (and other most- at-risk populations) in HIV \u2018hotspot\u2019 areas.62 In Ho Chi Minh City, Viet Nam, the Government\u2019s harm reduction programme has worked with a local community-based organization, the Blue Sky Club, to support health promotion efforts to reach MSM and transgender people. A series of meetings and discussion workshops involving community organizations and government departments \u2014 including representatives from the judiciary, law enforcement, health, and welfare agencies \u2014 have been held to explain the club\u2019s outreach and \u2018edutainment\u2019 work, and to seek their support in taking a \u2018hands off\u2019 approach to enforcement of the law for the sake of public health. As a result, MSM and transgender people are reported to face reduced threat of police harassment or detention for having condoms in their possession.63 Protective laws and policies Among ASEAN states, only the Philippines has taken action to provide legal protections to MSM and transgender people. Six cities in the Philippines have enacted local ordinances protecting people from discrimination on the grounds of their sexuality and/or gender identity.64 Several national anti- 59 Law No. 44/2008. 60 See, e.g., South Sumatra Provincial Regulation No. 13/2003 on Eradicating Immoral Acts in the Province of South Sumatra; Palembang City Regulation No. 2/2004; and the draft Sharia criminal regulations (Qanun Jinayat) of Aceh province of Indonesia. 61 See UNDP (2010), Legal environments, human rights and HIV responses among men who have sex with men and transgender people in Asia and the Pacific, Bangkok: UNDP. 62 FHI 360 and Ministry of Interior (2012), Baseline Survey on the Enabling Environment for Most at Risk Populations in Phnom Penh, Cambodia. Phnom Penh: FHI 360. 63 UNDP, USAID, UNAIDS, AIDS Project Management Group (2011), Towards Universal Access: Examples of municipal HIV programming for men who have sex with men and transgender persons in six Asian cities, Bangkok: UNDP, p. 34. 64 Angeles City, Bacolod City, Cebu, Dagupan City, Davao City, and Quezon City. See Passage of Cebu\u2019s anti-discrimination law lauded, Sun Star, 18 October 2012; Ordinance to protect gay rights in Cebu up in next PB session, Cebu Daily News, 17 February 2013; and LGBT leaders renew push for anti-discrimination bill, local ordinances, Outrage, 27 July 2013.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "efe6ec7f-a70e-48dd-943b-8a7d0305569a": {"__data__": {"id_": "efe6ec7f-a70e-48dd-943b-8a7d0305569a", "embedding": null, "metad